[Overview]

This paper presents concrete solutions to the climate crisis.

Core technology:
1. Ocean Breathing System
- Restoration
of ocean vertical circulation through deep-sea aeration - Fixed
5 tons of CO2 per unit per year - Significantly improved ocean absorption capacity with 100,000 units

2. Urban Environment Improvement System
- Soil Conversion and Greening
of Cities - Recycling-oriented Infrastructure
- Balance of CO2 Reduction and Absorption

Integrated effects:
- Reduce and absorb
9.5 billion tons of CO2 per year by 2050 - Stabilize global warming at +2.0°C
- Avoid tipping points

Features:
- Combination
of all proven technologies - Economically sustainable (35 years payback)
- Open source (no patent claims)
- Can be implemented by anyone

Implementation Plan:
- 2025: Prototype
- 2030: 1,000 units deployed
- 2050: 100,000 units

This paper is not a "paper for reading" but
a "blueprint for implementation".

