【overview】

This paper presents concrete solutions to the climate crisis.

Key technologies:
1. Ocean Breathing System
- Restoring ocean vertical circulation through deep sea aeration
- Fixing 5 tons of CO2 per unit per year
- Significantly improving ocean absorption capacity with 100,000 units

2. Urban environment improvement system
- Urban soil and greening
- Recycling infrastructure
- Achieving both CO2 reduction and absorption

Integrated effects:
- Reduction and absorption of 9.5 billion tons of CO2 per year by 2050
- Stabilization of global warming at +2.0°C
- Avoidance of tipping point

Features:
- A combination of all proven technologies
- Economically sustainable (35-year payback period)
- Open source (no patent claims)
- Anyone can implement it

Implementation plan:
- 2025: Prototype
- 2030: 1,000 units deployed
- 2050: 100,000 units achieved

This paper is not a "paper to read" but
a "blueprint for implementation."

