2025: Further record-breaking forecast
↓
Signs of acceleration
``` `

Accelerating ice sheet melt

**Greenland Ice Sheet:**

1990s
: Annual decrease of approximately 50 billion tons
2000s: Annual decrease of approximately 150 billion tons 2020s
: Annual decrease of approximately 300-400 billion tons
↓
Accelerating```

**Antarctic Ice Sheet:**

West
Antarctica: Rapid melting
Middle Antarctica: Previously considered stable, but signs of melting
↓ Accelerating
sea level rise

Frequent marine heatwaves

2023-2025
