The climate system is inherently nonlinear (chaotic)
↓
Behavior that cannot be predicted by linear models
↓
Sudden changes at tipping points
↓
Cannot be captured by conventional models

Lorentz's discovery (1963):

Weather is deterministic chaos
↓
Slight differences in initial conditions
↓
lead to unpredictable results
↓
"Butterfly effect"

