## 7.8 Installation and Operation

### 7.8.1 Installation Procedure

1. Land assembly:


Assemble the main components in the factory
: Upper
pyramid structure , Central core (
buoyancy body and control room)
, Lower pyramid skeleton
,
Inspection and testing

2. Sea transportation:

```
To the port by trailer
↓
To the sea by crane barge
↓
Or towed by self-
buoyancy```

3. Main pipe connection:


Connect a 250m pipe at sea ↓
Connect
25 x 10m sections in sequence
↓ Install
a spiral nozzle at the bottom

**4. Towing to installation area:**


Tugboat to installation point
↓
Accurate positioning with GPS coordinates
`` `

5. Anchoring:


Lower a weight anchor (500 kg) or
connect the cable to the submarine anchor construction (pre-construction
)



6. Operational test:

```
Check the operation of all systems
↓
Test run the compressor
↓
Check the communication system
↓
Check data transmission
↓
Start full-scale
operation```

**Duration:**

```
Per unit: Approximately 2-3 days (in good weather)
```

### 7.8.2 Operation and Monitoring

**Autonomous operation:**

```
Basically unmanned and autonomous operation
↓
Automatic control by microcomputer ↓
Alarm
only in case of abnormality```

**Remote Monitoring:**

```
Every hour: Location information transmission
Once a day: Operation data transmission
- Power generation amount -
Battery status
- Compressor operating time
- Weather data
↓
Centralized monitoring at the management center```

**Ocean observation data acquisition:**

```
Add sensors (optional):
- Water temperature (surface and deep)
- Salinity
- Dissolved oxygen
- pH
- Chlorophyll concentration
↓
Marine environment monitoring network
↓
Scientific data
accumulation```

### 7.8.3 Maintenance

**Regular inspection:**

Frequency
: Every 6 months to 1 year .
Visit
the site by work boat
.
Inspection items:
- Cleaning of solar panels
- Inspection of wind turbines
- Cleaning of tidal turbines (removal of attached organisms)
- Inspection of compressors
- Inspection of control systems
- Inspection of communication systems
- Check for structural damage
- Check the condition of pipes
.
Time required: Half a day to a full day per unit
.

**Parts Replacement:**


Battery: Every 5-7 years Compressor
: Every 10 years (overhaul)
Communications equipment: Every 10 years
Other: As
needed

**Service life:**

Main structure
: 30-40 years
Electrical system: 10-20 years (assuming replacement)
Overall
service life: 30 years or
more

### 7.8.4 Typhoon and severe weather countermeasures

**Design philosophy:**

"
Don't avoid the storm,
survive the storm.
"

**Structural measures:**

1.
Octahedron stability
- symmetrical top and bottom, less likely to capsize
- low center of gravity design

2. Buoyancy margin
- 200% safety factor
- Resists sinking caused by waves

3. Flexible pipe
- follows the waves
- not easily broken

4. Emergency Drainage - Automatic Drain Pump
in Case of Flooding

**Operational measures:**

When a
typhoon approaches:
↓
Predict in advance based on weather information
↓
Stop compressor
↓
Ensure battery charge status
↓
Maintain communication system
↓
Continue monitoring status
↓
After the typhoon passes:
↓
Automatic
or
remote
restart```

**Performance Targets:**

Even if a
typhoon hits, over 95% remain intact and continue to operate
.
5% suffer minor damage (repairable)
. Less than
1% are completely destroyed.

