# Chapter 10: Manufacturing and Economics

-----

10.1 Manufacturing Strategy Overview

### 10.1.1 Phased Manufacturing Planning

**Three Phases**

```
[Phase 1: Prototype]
2025-2026
Scale: 1-10 units
Purpose: Demonstration and improvement
Manufacturing method: Mainly manual

[Phase 2: Small-scale mass production]
2027-2028
Scale: 100-1,000 units/year
Objective: Establishment of manufacturing process
Manufacturing method: Semi-automation

[Phase 3: Large-scale mass production]
From 2029 onwards
Scale: 10,000 units per year or more
Objective: Global expansion
Manufacturing method: Fully
automated

-----

## 10.2 Manufacturing of Ocean Breathing Systems

10.2.1 Prototype Manufacturing (2025-2026)

**Place of manufacture:**

Selection criteria
:
- Close to the sea (for test installation)
- Industrial infrastructure available
- Availability of engineers
↓
Candidate locations:
- Yokohama (Japan)
- San Diego (USA)
- Singapore ,
etc.

**Manufacturing process:**

```
[Structure]
1. Frame production
- Aluminum alloy cutting and welding
- Precision processing
- Duration: 2 weeks

2. Buoyancy body assembly
- Foam molding
- FRP exterior lamination
- Duration: 1 week

3. Assembly
- Joining the frame and buoyancy body
- Waterproofing
- Duration: 1 week

[Energy System]
4. Solar panel installation
- wiring
- waterproofing
- Duration: 3 days

5. Wind and tidal turbine installation
- Operation check
- Duration: 3 days

6. Electrical system integration
- Battery installation
- Inverter and wiring
- Control panel assembly
- Duration: 1 week

[Pipe system]
7. Main pipe production
- HDPE pipe connection
- Reinforcement
- Duration: 1 week

8. Spiral nozzle production
- Stainless steel processing
- Precise spiral shape
- Duration: 1 week

9. Compressor installation
- Piping connection
- Operation test
- Duration: 3 days

[Control and Communication]
10. Control system integration
- Microcomputer and sensor installation
- Programming
- Duration: 1 week

11. Communication equipment installation
- Satellite communication equipment
- GPS/navigation lights
- Duration: 3 days

[Comprehensive Test]
12. Land test
- Check all system operation
- Waterproof test
- Duration: 1 week

13. Sea trials
- Buoyancy and stability confirmation
- Actual operation tests
- Duration: 2 weeks
↓
Total production time: Approximately 10-12 weeks per unit
````

**Cost (prototype):**


Material cost: $25,000 Labor
cost: $15,000 (2 skilled technicians x 12 weeks)
Equipment cost: $5,000 (tools, fixtures, etc.)
Testing cost: $10,000
↓
Total: $55,000/unit
↓
Expensive, but necessary for the learning process
```

### Fix: Manufacturing Cost

```
[Prototype (early stage)]
Conventional design: $55,000/unit

[Second generation (with nanobubbles)]
Additional costs:
- Nanobubble generator: $1,000
- Control system integration: $500
↓
Total additional: $1,500

Second generation costs:
Material costs: $13,500 ($12,000 + $1,500)
Labor costs: $1,500
Equipment depreciation costs: $1,500
Logistics costs: $500
Other: $1,000
↓
Total: $18,000/unit (for mass production)

However,
with improved performance:
- CO2 fixation: 5 → 7 tons/year (estimated)
- Dead zone elimination effect: 1.5 times
lower
Cost-effectiveness: improved
- Worth
the additional investment

10.2.2 Small-Scale Mass Production (2027-2028)

**Manufacturing base expansion:**

3-5
manufacturing sites : 200-300 units per year at each site
; total production: approximately 1,000 units per year




**Manufacturing process efficiency:**

```
[Standardization]
- Standardization of parts
- Documentation of manufacturing procedures
- Establishment of quality standards

[Development of dedicated jigs]
- Welding jigs
- Assembly jigs
- Inspection jigs
↓
Work time reduction: 30-40%

[Partial automation]
- Introduction of CNC processing machines
- Automatic welding
- Automatic wiring
↓
Work time reduction: Further 20-30%
↓
Production period: 12 weeks → 6 weeks/
unit

**Supply chain construction:**

```
[Parts Procurement]
Solar panels: 20% cost reduction through bulk orders
Wind turbines: Custom design for improved performance and cost reduction
Storage batteries: 30% cost reduction through mass production
HDPE pipes: 15% cost reduction through long-term contracts
↓
Material costs: $25,000 → $18,000/
unit```

**Cost (small scale production):**


Material costs: $18,000 Labor
costs: $6,000 (reduced through efficiency)
Equipment depreciation costs: $2,000
Other: $1,000
↓
Total: $27,000/unit
↓
Compared to prototype: Approximately 50%
reduction```

### 10.2.3 Large-scale mass production (2029 and beyond)

**Global manufacturing bases:**


20 locations worldwide : 500-1,000 units per year at each location
; total : 10,000-20,000 units per year




**Fully automated factory:**

```
[Robotics]
- Welding robots
- Assembly robots
- Inspection robots
- AGVs (automated guided vehicles)
↓
Personnel: 2 people/unit → 0.2 people/unit

[Digital Twin]
- Fully digitalized from design to manufacturing
- Optimization through simulation
- Real-time quality control

[IoT integration]
- Data collection for all processes
- Production optimization using AI
- Predictive maintenance
↓
Manufacturing period: 6 weeks → 2 weeks/unit
Defect rate: 5% → below 1%
```

Economies of scale:

```
[Bulk Procurement]
Bulk ordering of parts: Further cost reduction of 20-30%

[Development of dedicated parts]
Dedicated design instead of generic products:
Improved performance + reduced costs

[Vertical integration]
In-house production of some parts:
Cost reduction + quality improvement
↓
Material cost: $18,000 → $12,000/
unit```

**Cost (large scale production):**


Material costs: $12,000 Labor
costs: $1,500 (significant reduction)
Equipment depreciation costs: $1,500
Logistics costs: $500
Other: $1,000
↓
Total: $16,500/unit
↓
Compared to prototype: 70% reduction
Compared to small-scale mass production: 40%
reduction```

