happen once the entire system is operational
. ↓ Only partial benefits
during the phase-in period ↓ Full benefits: 2040s and beyond .




-----

10.6 Cost-saving innovations

### 10.6.1 Materials Innovation

**Ocean Breathing System:**

```
[Lightweight]
Present: Aluminum alloy frame
↓
Future: Carbon fiber composite
↓
Effects:
- 50% weight reduction
- 20% strength improvement
- Cost: Initially high, but equivalent with mass production

[Longer life]
Present: 30 years service life
↓
Future: 50 years with new materials
↓
Life cycle costs: 40%
reduction```

### 10.6.2 Manufacturing innovation

**3D Printing:**

Complex shaped parts
(spiral nozzles, etc.)
↓
One-piece molding using 3D printing
↓
Benefits:
- Manufacturing time: 50% reduction
- Material loss: 70% reduction
- Performance: Optimized
shape```

**AI design optimization:**

AI
-based design search
:
Automatically evaluate thousands to tens of thousands of design proposals
.
Discover the optimal design
.
Results:
Performance: 10-20% improvement
. Cost: 10-15% reduction
.

### 10.6.3 Energy Efficiency Improvements

**High-efficiency solar cells:**

Present
: Conversion efficiency 20%
↓
Future: 30% with perovskite solar cells, etc.
↓
Effect:
- 1.5 times more power generation in the same area
- Or the same output with a 33% reduction in
area```

**High-efficiency compressor:**

Present
: Power consumption 5 kW
↓
Future: 3.5 kW with magnetic bearings and ultra-precision machining
↓
Effects:
- 30% reduction in power consumption
- Double maintenance
intervals```

