10.7 Quality Control and Standardization

### 10.7.1 Quality Standards

**Performance standards:**

```
Ocean Breathing System:
- CO2 fixation capacity: 5±0.5 ton/year/unit
- Operation rate: 90% or more
- Service life: 30 years or more
- Typhoon resistance: Maximum wind speed 60 m/s
````

**Safety standards:**

- Navigational
safety (navigation lights, reflectors)
- Environmental safety (minimizing impact on marine life)
- Electrical safety (preventing electric shock
)

### 10.7.2 International Standardization

**Standardization by ISO etc.:**

```
[Design Standards]
ISO ○○○○: Marine Regeneration System Design Standards

[Test Method]
ISO △△△△: Performance evaluation test method

[Safety Standards]
ISO □□□□: Safety standards for offshore installations
↓
Globally common standards
↓
Interoperability
↓
Cost reduction
````

### 10.7.3 Certification System

**Third Party Certification:**

```
Performance and safety certification by an independent organization
↓
Only certified products can be installed
↓
Quality assurance
↓ Increased
market reliability```

