# Chapter 11: Implementation Roadmap

-----

## 11.1 Overall Timeline

### 11.1.1 Five Phases

```
[Phase 0: Preparation]
Q1-Q2 2025 (6 months)
Objectives: Establishment of structure, fundraising, finalization of design

[Phase 1: Demonstration Period]
Q3 2025-Q4 2026 (18 months)
Objectives: Prototype demonstration, improvement, and increased awareness

[Phase 2: Launch]
2027-2028 (2 years)
Objectives: Establishment of mass production system, initial deployment, standardization

[Phase 3: Expansion]
2029-2035 (7 years)
Objectives: Large-scale deployment, global dissemination, effectiveness demonstration

[Phase 4: Maturity]
2036-2050 (15 years)
Objectives: Full deployment, continuous improvement, goal
achievement```

-----

11.2 Phase 0: Preparation (Q1-Q2 2025)

### 11.2.1 Establishing an organizational structure

**Establishment of an international consortium:**

```
[Participating entities]
- Research institutions (ocean research institutes, climate research institutes, etc.)
- Technology companies (renewable energy, shipbuilding, construction, etc.)
- Financial institutions (green banks, etc.)
- International organizations (UNEP, etc.)
- NGOs (environmental organizations, etc.)
- National governments

[Organizational structure]
Board of Directors: Decision-making
↓
Technical Committee: Design and standardization
Funding Committee: Fundraising and management
Implementation Committee: Project execution
Public Relations Committee: Information dissemination
↓
National branches: Regional
expansion```

**Headquarters establishment:**

```
Candidate locations:
- Geneva (many UN agencies, neutral)
- Tokyo (technologically advanced, Pacific coast)
- Singapore (maritime nation, Asian hub)
↓
or multiple
locations```

