11.3 Phase 1: Demonstration Period (Q3 2025 - Q4 2026)

### 11.3.1 Prototype No. 1 (Q3-Q4 2025)

**Manufacturing:**

Location
: Yokohama (hypothetical)
Period: July-September 2025 (3 months
)

**Test Setup:**


Location Selection:
Tokyo Bay, Sagami Bay, etc. ↓
Conditions
:
- Depth of 250m or more
- Away from shipping routes
- Ocean observation data available
- Good access (for monitoring)

[Installation]
October 2025
↓
Towing and installation: 3
days

**Initial Test (3 months):**

October
-December 2025
↓
Items to check:
- Buoyancy and stability
- Power generation capacity
- Compressor operation
- Communication system
- Typhoon resistance (with luck/unlucky)
↓
Data collection:
- Hourly operation data
- Weather data
- Oceanographic data (water temperature, salinity, DO, etc.)
```

### 11.3.2 Effectiveness Measurement (Q1-Q4 2026)

Marine Environmental Monitoring:

```
[Survey items]
Plankton:
- Before installation
- 3 months after
installation - 6 months after installation
- 12 months after installation
↓
Species composition, number of individuals, chlorophyll concentration

Water quality:
- Nutrient concentration (surface-deep)
- Dissolved oxygen
- pH
- Turbidity
↓
Measure once a week

Fish fauna:
- Acoustic survey
- Underwater survey
- Fish catch survey (with cooperation from neighboring fishermen)
↓
Monthly
survey```

**Evaluation of CO2 fixation amount:**

```
[Method]
Change in plankton amount
↓
Carbon equivalent
↓
Estimation of annual fixed amount

[Prediction]
Target: 5 ton CO2/year/unit
↓
Comparison with actual measurements
↓
Model
correction```

### 11.3.3 Prototype 2-5 (2026)

**Improved production:**

```
Improvements based on data from Unit 1
↓
Unit 2: Manufactured in Q1 2026, installed in Q2
Unit 3: Manufactured in Q2 2026, installed in Q3 Units
4-5: Manufactured in Q3 2026, installed in Q4
↓
Installation in different ocean areas:
- Sea of ​​Japan
- Pacific Ocean (Kuroshio Current region)
- East China Sea
- Seto Inland Sea
↓ Demonstration
in diverse environments```

