## 15.4 The Migration Process

### 15.4.1 2025-2030: Emergence period

```
[Technology]
- Ocean Breathing System: Demonstration → Initial deployment
- Eco-District: Pilot → Expansion
- Renewable energy: Rapid adoption

[Society]
- Spreading awareness
- Practiced by leading individuals and organizations
- Not yet mainstream

[Economy]
- Time for initial investment
- Growth of green businesses
- Job creation begins

[Culture]
- Rising environmental awareness
- but not yet established
↓
The beginning of change
````

### 15.4.2 2030-2040: The transition period

```
[Technology]
- Ocean Breathing System: Large-scale deployment
- Eco-city: Expanding
- Circular system: Standardization

[Society]
- Majority practice
- Young generation leads
- Community revitalization

[Economy]
- Circular economy becomes mainstream
- Decline of fossil fuel industry
- Growth of green economy

[Culture]
- Sustainability becomes "normal"
- Differences in values ​​between generations (older vs. newer generations)
↓ Accelerating
change```

### 15.4.3 2040-2050: Establishment Period

```
[Technology]
- Ocean Breathing System: 100,000 units achieved
- Eco-city: Standard
- Technology maturity

[Society]
- Practiced by all generations
- Sustainability is the norm
- Community stability

[Economy]
- Establishing a circular economy
- Sustainable growth
- Reducing inequality

[Culture]
- Sustainability becomes a culture
- Passing it on to the next generation
↓
Establishing a new civilization
````

