The Ocean Breathing System's blueprints, specifications, etc. comply with
the CERN Open Hardware Licence Version 2 - Strongly Reciprocal (CERN-OHL-S v2) .

This means:
- It can be freely manufactured and sold
- It can be improved
- However, the improved version must also be open source (reciprocity)

Patents:
The basic technology will not be patented and will be in the public domain. However, defensive patents may be obtained
to prevent malicious patent acquisition by third parties . In such cases, the technology will still be licensed royalty-free .



